communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The news report does not say if the _C. difficile_ isolates from the 57
Nanaimo patients are genetically related, or if they are indeed
_Clostridium difficile_ ribotype 027, which characteristically
hyper-produce toxin and cause diarrhea and colitis that is associated with
increased morbidity, mortality, and poor response to antimicrobial therapy.
This particular ribotype 027 is characteristically resistant to
fluoroquinolones, the use of which is a risk factor for acquisition of _C.
difficile_-associated diarrhea and colitis due to ribotype 027.

From a prior ProMED-mail post -- Clostridium difficile, ribotype 027 - UK:
(N. Ireland) 20080207.0498:
"_Clostridium difficile_ is the most common cause of bacterial diarrhea and
pseudomembranous colitis in hospitalized patients, and antimicrobial drug
therapy is the most important risk factor associated with the acquisition
of _C. difficile_.

"Preventing the spread of _C. difficile_ in health care facilities involves
clinical and microbiologic surveillance of hospitalized patients with
diarrhea for _C. difficile_ and heightened infection control measures,
including prompt isolation of patients with _C. difficile_-positive
diarrhea or cohorting, where isolation rooms are not available, combined
with particular emphasis on hand hygiene and control of the inappropriate
use of antimicrobial agents
(<http://www.shea-online.org/Assets/files/position_papers/Cldiff95.PDF>)."

A map of the Canadian province of British Columbia can be found at
<http://atlas.nrcan.gc.ca/site/english/maps/reference/provincesterritories/british_columbia/referencemap_image_view>.
Nanaimo, with a population of about 80 000 residents, is located on the
east coast of Vancouver Island, 55 km across the Strait of Georgia from
city of Vancouver, British Columbia (see map at
<http://www.cityofnanaimo.com/>). Nanaimo is the second largest city on
Vancouver Island. Vancouver Island, about the same size as Holland, is the
largest North American Island in the Pacific Ocean. - Mod.ML]
